< [ DOCS ] >

[ v ( o ) ]

: v(o) is a function that is querySelector function but shorter.

[ vs ( o ) ]

: vs(o) is a function that is querySelector function to select the structure of HTML but shorter.

( If you want to use like to specify body, you need to do like this : vs('body') and not like this : v('body') )

[ vn ( o ) ]

: vn(o) is a function that is use to create new element.

[ va ( s , o ) ]

: va(s, o) is a function that is use to add child to the parent element but shorter.

[ vst ( s , o ) ]

: vst(s, o) is a function that is use to set text (innerHTML) on the element.

[ vid ( s , o ) ]

: vid(s, o) is a function that is use to set id of the element.

[ vc ( s , o ) ]

: vc(s, o) is a function that is use to set class of the element.

[ vae ( s , e , f ) ]

: vae(s, e, f) is a function that is addEventListener but shorter.

[ vow ( d ) ]

: vow(d) is a function that is use to open a file.

[ vdl ( f ) ]

: vdl(f) is a function that is use to download file.

< [ DOCS EXAMPLES ] >

[ v ( o ) ]

: const myDiv = v("#myDiv")

[ vs ( o ) ]

: const body = vs("body")

[ vn ( o ) ]

: const newheading1 = vn("h1")

[ va ( s , o ) ]

: va(vs("body"), myDiv)

[ vst ( s , o ) ]

: vst(myDiv, "Hello World!")

[ vid ( s , o ) ]

: vid(myDiv, "myID")

[ vc ( s , o ) ]

: vc(myDiv, "myCLASS")

[ vae ( s , e , f ) ]

: vae(myDiv, "click", ()=> { myDiv.remove() })

[ vow ( d ) ]

: vow("my-file-to-open")

[ vdl ( f ) ]

: vdl("my-file-to-download")